- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses a numerical method for solving partial differential equations (PDEs) using deep neural networks (DNNs) and compares it to conventional finite element and finite volume methods. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses DNNs to solve PDEs and discusses the use of supervised training on synthetic experimental data to enrich the model PDE system. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies the DNN method to analyze solutions to compressible Euler equations and compressible magnetohydrodynamics (MHD), which are commonly used in computational engineering and science. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): There is no direct connection to social and information networks in the paper, but the use of DNNs for data enrichment and integration could potentially be applied in this field. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses DNNs to solve PDEs and discusses the use of supervised training on synthetic experimental data, which are both applications of AI.
